Description: Woodwork-filled brew pub with a massive beer list offering creative pub fare & brunch items.

summary.snippet: "Huge selection of delicious beer, tasty burgers and great service."
"Service midweek was a bit slow, but they had minimal staff."
"Got food poisoning from the "crack fries" and a frat boy threw up on my shoes."

most_relevant.description:
Average food. It’s a one time try.
Nothing special, but not bad too.
Burgers are really good. They don’t cost too much. I got one for $13.

If you are a beer lover, there are a lot of options for you. You should see the menu and you will know.

One of the best times to visit this place is at night.
Chill with your friends, drink with your partner or just hang alone at the bar, this place offers it all.
I tried lobster mac, and it tasted good.  Creamy a little but overall it was worth the money. The drink was too strong, that is a good thing. 😂
Paloma was good.

I think they were short-staffed at night.
Good place, with chill vibes.

Chill ambiance with really good food-

Hopcat’s food ever disappoints. The Nashville hot chicken sandwich is just… wow. Juicy, fried, tasty, probably not healthy, but it tastes so good. Always loved the service over here too. You won’t be disappointed.
Had several visits here, serves good bar food and great selection of ales and ciders. Service midweek was a bit slow, but they had minimal staff.

The food is generally very good and hearty. Perfect for the cold midwestern weather. The fries, in particular are worth the price of admission. They are very crispy, soft on the inside, and perfectly seasoned.
The portions are also generous.

The last couple of times, the service was a bit slow and disappointing, but nothing to be too worried about. Overall a good reliable restaurant for pub-style food and good beer.

I came in the other night and had Kaylee as my server. She was the best! She was very cheerful and made sure we were taken care of all night. She went above and beyond all night. She even suggested we try the cookie dough cheese cake, and it was the best decision I made all week. 100% will be returning and asking for Kaylee!

Drove from toledo ann harbor and it was worth it the food was great and the drinks . I would get the elote queso and the tropical blue drink . Burgers and chicken sandwiches were great . Tried the pickleback and wasn't sure about everything pickle flavored, but it was great .

Very disappointed... I had high expectations going in because of my previous visit and the reputation of this establishment 🍺 That being said, the service 🔧 was ATROCIOUS. We got in at 6:30 and left at 8:30 because of how slow 🦥 it was. The place wasn't even busy! It took forever to order and even longer for the food 🍗 to eventually come out. On top of that, the waitress didn't even know the cost of add-ons! That's awful! The fries 🍟 were the only redeeming part of this experience...
